    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Components of a loom, comprising sticks inserted close to the heddle rod of a frame loom. By pushing down or pulling up on the shed stick, the weaver forms a countershed.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000132/Suzzallo-UW</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000050842/Broudy, The Book of Looms (1979)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Een stok die men dicht bij de hevelroede van een weefraam insteekt. Door de ophaler omhoog te trekken of naar beneden te duwen creëert men een vak.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
